---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Parrish Tree Removal | Tree Service Guidance in Parrish, FL"
  description="Learn more about Parrish Tree Removal and the approach to tree service planning, estimates, and project guidance."
>
  <section class="internal-hero">
    <div class="internal-hero-shell">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>Helpful tree service information for Parrish property owners</h1>
      <p>
        Parrish Tree Removal focuses on clear information, practical next steps, and a
        smoother estimate experience for common residential tree projects.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="page-shell">
    <section class="page-section">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 class="section-title-reveal">What Homeowners Usually Need</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="stack-grid">
        <article class="stack-panel">
          <h3>Help identifying the right service</h3>
          <p>
            The first question is often whether a tree needs removal, trimming,
            stump work, or storm-related cleanup.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="stack-panel">
          <h3>Clear next-step guidance</h3>
          <p>
            Projects move faster when the estimate request already includes useful
            details about access, urgency, and property layout.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="stack-panel">
          <h3>Simple communication</h3>
          <p>
            Good estimate support starts with straightforward information, not
            confusing steps or vague project descriptions.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page-section">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 class="section-title-reveal">How Requests Are Framed</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="page-card page-card-soft">
        <ul class="list-copy">
          <li>Property owners describe the issue and the location on the lot.</li>
          <li>Tree size, access, and urgency are used to shape the next conversation.</li>
          <li>Removal, trimming, stump work, and cleanup can all be discussed together.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
